<p>
I struggled with this one. I was not sure how to explain that the Law was weak or was the one that failed, when what it means is that we were weak and failed to keep the law.
</p>

<p>
I have “God was able,” but the verb that goes with “God” is “condemned.” I didn&#039;t know how to show this without rewriting the whole verse.
</p>

<p>
“Condemned in the flesh.” I think the UDB is off on its translation. “When he did this, he also showed that our sins are truly wicked, and that anyone who sins deserves to be punished.” I think this is missing the point. The Law already told everyone that sin deserved to be punished. I think this phrase means sin itself was judged, condemned, and broken in the body of Christ (i.e. in his flesh). We didn&#039;t need to be told sin was bad, we needed someone to help us stop sinning.
</p>
