Your notes

**likeness of sinful flesh** - When Jesus was on earth, he looked like any other man (“likeness of”). But he did not have the sinful nature (“sinful flesh”) that we have.
    
**in the flesh** - The word “flesh” refers to the human nature apart from God. By making his Son an offering for our sin, God condemned the sin of the sinful nature.
    
**according to the flesh** - This is similar to “in the flesh,” but it refers to the way of life of people who do not know God, who make selfish decisions and wrong choices, who do not obey God's commands. (Verse 5 explains what it means to live “according to the flesh.”)
    
**according to the Spirit** - This is the opposite of “according to the flesh.” It refers a believer in Christ who is obedient to the Spirit of God and God's laws. (Verse 5 clarifies what it means to live “according to the Spirit.”)

